          "id": "pa-slide-1",
          "title": "The past form changes inside the verb",
          "description": "Unlike the present-tense lesson, these examples are not mainly about a separate marker at the front. Pay attention to how the past verb itself shifts from one person to the next.",
          "focusPoints": [
            "`imi/imid` = I came",
            "`timi/timid` is used for `you` and `she`",
            "`yimi/yimid` marks `he`"
          ],
